<h2 id="product-sorting" sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="246">Product sorting</h2>
<p sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="248">In the <em sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="248">Product sorting</em> panel, you can define:</p>
<ul sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250">
<li sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250"><p sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250">Select the <strong sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250">Allow product sorting</strong> checkbox to enable a product sorting option on the categories and manufacturers pages. You can activate/deactivate sorting by <em sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250">Position</em>, <em sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250">Name</em>, <em sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250">Price</em>, and <em sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="250">Date of creation</em>.</p>
<div class="NOTE" sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="252">
<h5>Note</h5>
<p sourcefile="en/running-your-store/catalog/catalog-settings.md" sourcestartlinenumber="253">Selecting the value &quot;Position&quot; means that there will be no restrictions on the sorting of products.</p>
